cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with cross-lingual transfer of syntactic dependency knowledge. Additionally, the use of cross-lingual word embeddings further supports this categorization. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a method for improving the accuracy of cross-lingual parsing, which is a common task in natural language processing. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper leverages cross-lingual word embeddings for transferring syntactic knowledge. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper may involve the use of neural networks for cross-lingual parsing. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely sub-category as the paper may involve techniques for retrieving and aligning source and target words in the treebanks.
